<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870811-0147 </DOCNO><HL> June Retail Sales in the U.K.</HL><DD> 08/11/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EUROP </IN><DATELINE> LONDON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   June retail sales in Britain, calculated on a volume basis, were revised to show gains of 5% from a year earlier, unchanged from an earlier estimate, and 3.2% from May, up from 3.1% reported earlier, the Department of Trade and Industry said.    In value terms, sales increased about 7% in June from a year earlier, the department added. </TEXT></DOC>